Title: 22C:145 Artificial intelligence I - Fall 1994
Body: Date: Wed, 20 Nov 1996 23:17:27 GMT Server: NCSA/1.5 Content-type: text/html 22C:145 Artificial intelligence I - Fall 1994 22C:145 Artificial intelligence I - Fall 1994 Instructor: Maria Paola Bonacina (bonacina@cs.uiowa.edu) Class Meetings: 1:30pm - 2:30pm MWF in 113 MacLean Hall Objectives of the course: to give a rigorous introduction to the field of Artificial Intelligence, that offers to the student opportunities for abstract thinking, problem solving and programming, and serves as a foundation for further studies.
